name: Summer Night Solitude
description: It was the Fourth of July and the entire downtown area was covered in the lingering smoke of fireworks being set off in all directions. It floated gently like a blanket of fog in a portside town. Its serenity was in stark contrast to the echoes of gunpowder exploding both faintly and deafeningly in relation to its proximity. This scene provided a moment of visual calm that dampened the effect of the cacophony of tiny bombs. Taken in Pontiac, Michigan, USA in 2021. 3600x5400px 300dpi jpg
